cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV

This paper deals with natural language understanding for robots, which falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper focuses on interpreting natural language commands. The use of reward functions and a state-of-the-art planner suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The application of the approach to robot-simulation results suggests that it may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The use of deep learning techniques and neural networks suggests that it may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
